cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) because it proposes a pattern-aware architecture for CNN accelerators. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because it evaluates the proposed method on VGG-16 and ResNet-18, which are popular CNN models for computer vision tasks. Additionally, it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it proposes a pruning method for model compression, which is a common technique in machine learning and neural networks. Finally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it presents a hardware implementation of the proposed method.
